  "local_port": 59008,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I use the Wi-Fi on my windows phone (wp8.1) in BHU (hostels, departments, library)?",
  "response": "To use Wi-Fi on your Windows Phone 8.1 in Banaras Hindu University (BHU), or any other location like hostels, departments, or libraries, you can follow these general steps:\n\n### Step 1: Enable Wi-Fi\n\n1. **Open the Settings app**: Swipe down from the top of the screen to reveal the Quick Settings. Tap on the gear icon to access Settings.\n2. **Go to Wi-Fi**: Look for the \u201cNetwork & wireless\u201d section and tap on \u201cWi-Fi.\u201d\n3. **Turn on Wi-Fi**: Toggle the Wi-Fi switch to ON.\n\n### Step 2: Connect to the Network\n\n1. **Select the Network**: Your phone will scan for available Wi-Fi networks. Find the network you want to connect to (e.g., \"BHU Wi-Fi\" or a specific department/library network).\n2. **Enter Password**: If the network is secured, a prompt will appear for you to enter the Wi-Fi password. Obtain the password from your department, hostel management, or library staff if needed.\n3. **Connect**: After entering the password, tap on \u201cConnect.\u201d\n\n### Step 3: Open Browser for Authentication\n\n1. **Open a Browser**: Once connected, open your preferred web browser (like Internet Explorer).\n2. **Authenticate**: You might be redirected to a login page for the university\u2019s network. If not, try navigating to any website.\n3. **Log In**: Enter your university credentials as required (username, student ID, password) to authenticate with the Wi-Fi network.\n\n### Step 4: Troubleshooting (if needed)\n\n- **Check Network Availability**: Make sure the network is operational and that you are within range.\n- **Forget the Network**: If you are having issues, you might want to forget the network and try reconnecting. To do this, go to the Wi-Fi settings, tap and hold on the network name, and select \"Forget.\"\n- **Check for Data Limits**: Ensure you are within any limits set by the university for Wi-Fi usage.\n- **Contact Support**: If problems persist, reach out to the IT support team at BHU for assistance.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Use Campus Resources**: BHU might provide IT support or guides specific to their networks. Check the official website or student resources.\n- **Stay Updated**: Sometimes networks require updated apps or additional configurations, so it\u2019s good to check for any announcements or updates regarding the network.\n  \nBy following these steps, you should be able to connect your Windows Phone 8.1 to the Wi-Fi networks available in BHU.",
